This field also links to hubspot via the hubspot API and, if the two are different, will ensure there are separate contacts made for the student and the payer to track each individually.

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student
Select options: 1SM, Comprehensive 1, Comprehensive 2, Comprehensive 3, Tutoring only
Description: This is a very outdated set of data but we still use it very heavily. The status the student has in this field tells us whether they have access to our course or not. While other statuses are available, I've listed the ones that matter in the 'Select options' column.
Technical notes:
If the student has Comprehensive 1, Comprehensive 2, or Comprehensive 3, in this field and DO NOT HAVE 'Bootcamp' in the 'Bootcamp Status' field, then they have access to the Comprehensive Course. 

If they do have 'Bootcamp' in the 'Bootcamp Status' field then they do not have access to the Comprehensive Course.

If they have Tutoring only then they do not have Comprehensive Course access or Bootcamp access. 

In the new schema, we need to create separate boolean fields for each of these: 'Comprehensive Course', 'Bootcamp', and 'Tutoring'
New schema notes: In the new schema, this should become a Boolean field for the Comprehensive Course. The bootcamp is discussed in more detail below.

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student

Description: Single select field that indicates the level of access students from the emory course had. We'll do this differently in the future but we should still retain this data just in case.

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student
Select options: Bootcamp, No
Description: Bootcamp' means the student has access to the Bootcamp in the Boolean variable described previously for the new schema. If this says 'Bootcamp' then it means the student certainly does NOT have comprehensive course access.
New schema notes: We have a variety of Bootcamps so it would be better to have a field where we indicate which bootcamp the student has access to. That said, indicating that they have signed up for the Bootcamp before isn't a bad idea but just having a boolean like this is not much information. I'm going to make the next field one that actually isn't in airtable but is how we should think about the Bootcamp moving forward

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student
Description:
This is a new field (not currently in airtable) but it will completely fix the issue we have and we're going to need to take data from the current airtable setup to get this to make sense.

The bootcamp_course table will be for the Bootcamp what the Courses1 table is for the Comprehensive Course. Each record will be a separate course that students can sign up for. 

The first two courses in that list will be 'gen1_bootcamp' and 'summer2025_bootcamp'. These will link to all students who have 'Bootcamp' in their 'Bootcamp Status' field as well as 'Gen 1' or 'Summer 2025' in their 'Bootcamp Assigned' field.

The third course in the 'bootcamp_course' table will be 'wbc25' and people who have 'Bootcamp Assigned' as 'Winter 2025' will be assigned to this course cohort. From there, additional bootcamps will be added and this will be the only field that matters when looking to determine whether a student has bootcamp access or not. That way we don't have to include 'Bootcamp Status' or 'Bootcamp Assigned' fields in the new schema.
New schema notes:
This is a new field (not currently in airtable) but it will completely fix the issue we have and we're going to need to take data from the current airtable setup to get this to make sense.

The bootcamp_course table will be for the Bootcamp what the Courses1 table is for the Comprehensive Course. Each record will be a separate course that students can sign up for. 

The first two courses in that list will be 'gen1_bootcamp' and 'summer2025_bootcamp'. These will link to all students who have 'Bootcamp' in their 'Bootcamp Status' field as well as 'Gen 1' or 'Summer 2025' in their 'Bootcamp Assigned' field.

The third course in the 'bootcamp_course' table will be 'winter2025_bootcamp' and people who have 'Bootcamp Assigned' as 'Winter 2025' will be assigned to this course cohort. From there, additional bootcamps will be added and this will be the only field that matters when looking to determine whether a student has bootcamp access or not. That way we don't have to include 'Bootcamp Status' or 'Bootcamp Assigned' fields in the new schema.

Table description: Each record corresponds to one student
Select options: Clear, Graduated, Delinquent, Closed
Description: This field automatically changes to 'Delinquent' when a payment fails for a student on a payment plan. It is then updated to turn back to 'Clear' when the payment succeeds later. if a student quits the program and gets a refund it changes to 'Closed'. And if a student finishes the program then it changes to 'Graduated'. Only 'Clear' or empty status in this field allows a student to see the student portal
New schema notes: Might want to add a separate field for Graduated but I'm honestly not sure about that
